Sentencas: To overcome significantly sluggish oxygen-ion conduction in the electrolytes of low-temperature solid-oxide fuel cells (SOFCs), numerous researchers have devoted considerable effort to fabricating the electrolytes as thin as possible.
Titulo: Nanocrystal Engineering of Thin-Film Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolytes for Low-Temperature Solid-Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: However, thickness is not the only factor that affects the electrolyte performance; roughness, grain size, and internal film stress also play a role.
Titulo: Nanocrystal Engineering of Thin-Film Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolytes for Low-Temperature Solid-Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In this study, yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) was deposited via a reactive sputtering process to fabricate high-performance thin-film electrolytes.
Titulo: Nanocrystal Engineering of Thin-Film Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolytes for Low-Temperature Solid-Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Various sputtering chamber pressures (5, 10, and 15 mTorr) were investigated to improve the electrolytes.
Titulo: Nanocrystal Engineering of Thin-Film Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolytes for Low-Temperature Solid-Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: As a result, high surface area, large grain size, and residual tensile stress were successfully obtained by increasing the sputtering pressure.
Titulo: Nanocrystal Engineering of Thin-Film Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolytes for Low-Temperature Solid-Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: To clarify the correlation between the microstructure and electrolyte performance, a YSZ thin-film electrolyte was applied to anodized aluminum oxide-supported SOFCs composed of conventional electrode materials which are Ni and Pt as the anode and the cathode, respectively.
Titulo: Nanocrystal Engineering of Thin-Film Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolytes for Low-Temperature Solid-Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The thin-film SOFC with YSZ deposited at 15 mTorr exhibited the lowest ohmic resistance and, consequently, the highest maximum power density (493 mW/cm2) at 500 & DEG;C whose performance is more than five times higher than that of the cell with YSZ deposited at 5 mTorr (94.1 mW/cm2).
Titulo: Nanocrystal Engineering of Thin-Film Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolytes for Low-Temperature Solid-Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Despite the basic electrode materials, exceptionally high performance at low operating temperature was achieved via controlling the single fabrication condition for the electrolyte.
Titulo: Nanocrystal Engineering of Thin-Film Yttria-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolytes for Low-Temperature Solid-Oxide Fuel Cells
